'YES NO' GETS A YES OR NO RESPONSEFROM THE USER; ACCEPTING Y; y; N; ORn AND   IGNORING ALL OTHER KEYSEXCEPT RETURN;  WHICH ACCEPTS THEDEFAULT RESPONSE.AFTER 'BLOAD YES NO'; CALL IT LIKETHIS:     CALL 768;n;$var...WHERE n IS THE DEFAULT RESPONSEOF   'Y' OR 'N' AND $var IS THESTRING       VARIABLE THAT SHOULD BEASSIGNED THE    VALUE OF THE USER'SRESPONSE.SEE 'YES NO DEMO' FOR AN EXAMPLE.ALSO; THE BINARY CODE ISRELOCATABLE.